claim: Flublok is produced using a novel production platform in which recombinant HA is expressed in insect cells using a baculovirus expression vector system (BEVS).
explanation: Table listing various licensed influenza vaccines (IIV4, ccIIV4, HD-IIV4, aIIV4, RIV4, LAIV4), detailing trade names (manufacturers), presentations, age indications, HA content per dose, administration route, and mercury content. Under RIV4 (recombinant HA vaccine), Flublok Quadrivalent (Sanofi Pasteur) is listed with a 0.5-mL prefilled syringe, age ≥18 years, 45 µg/0.5 mL, IM. Evidence: Identifies Flublok as a recombinant HA vaccine but does not describe its production platform or mention insect cells or BEVS. The table does not support the claim because, although it labels Flublok as a recombinant HA vaccine, it does not provide any information on its production using a novel insect cell baculovirus expression vector system, and thus does not support the claim. Note: None
